ta if the nuclear EOS is stiff. Also, we show that\nlow-mass twins and especially triplets proliferate the number of combinations\nof possible types of stars that can undergo a merger event, the maximal number\nbeing six in the case of triplets. The prospects for uncovering the first-order\nphase transition(s) to and in quark matter via measurements of tidal\ndeformabilities in merger events are discussed.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 1 Nov 2019 09:29:11 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 21 Feb 2020 14:15:07 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 20 Mar 2020 16:59:04 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-03-23"}
