amic outflow that transports a\nsignificant amount of Ca II into the upper atmosphere. The prominent Ca II\ndetection with the lack of significant Ca I detection implies that calcium is\nmostly ionized in the upper atmospheres of the two planets.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 1 Nov 2019 13:52:17 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-12-11"}
